Zimbabwean politician Edgar Tekere
died of cancer today aged 74,  Newsday  said on its website.  The Harare-based newspaper said Tekere died in a clinic in
the eastern city of Mutare. Tekere was a founding member of
President  Robert Mugabe â€™s  Zimbabwe  African National Union-
Patriotic Front party, Newsday reported. The two men broke their
alliance when Tekere emerged as a rival to Mugabe, according to
